<topic id="topic_A456CF4C97AB5560" xml:lang="en-US">
	<title>Fig testing</title>
	<shortdesc>The figure (&lt;fig&gt;) element is a display context (sometimes called an “exhibit”) with an optional title for a
wide variety of content. Most commonly, the figure element contains an image element (a graphic or
artwork), but it can contain several kinds of text objects as well. A title is placed inside the figure element
to provide a caption to describe the content.</shortdesc>

	<body>
        <section>
            <title>GIF sample</title>
            <p>This is simple GIF sample</p>
            <fig expanse="column" id="fig_99302FCD39DF45EA32FD">
                <title>Flower</title>
                <desc>The &lt;desc&gt; element contains the description of the current element. A description should provide more information than the title. This is its behavior in fig/table/linklist, for example. In xref/link, it provides a description of the target; processors that support it may choose to display this as hover help. In object, it contains alternate content for use when in contexts that cannot display the object.</desc>
                <image href="image/flower.gif" alt="Flower">
                    <alt>Here is a description!</alt>
                </image>
            </fig>
        </section>
        <section>
            <title>%display-atts; sample</title>
            <fig frame="all" >
                <title>Flower frame='all'</title>
                <image href="image/flower.gif" alt="Flower" placement="break"/>
            </fig>
            <fig frame="topbot" >
                <title>Flower frame='topbot'</title>
                <image href="image/flower.gif" alt="Flower" placement="break"/>
            </fig>
        </section>
        <section>
            <title>image attribute sample</title>
            <fig frame="all" >
                <title>Flower width="3cm"</title>
                <image href="image/flower.gif" alt="Flower" width="3cm"/>
            </fig>
            <p></p>
            <fig frame="all" >
                <title>Flower height="5cm"</title>
                <image href="image/flower.gif" alt="Flower" height="5cm"/>
            </fig>
            <p></p>
            <fig frame="all" >
                <title>Flower width="3cm", height="5cm"</title>
                <image href="image/flower.gif" alt="Flower" width="3cm" height="5cm"/>
            </fig>
            <p></p>
            <fig frame="all" >
                <title>Flower scale="200"</title>
                <image href="image/flower.gif" alt="Flower" scale="200"/>
            </fig>
            <p></p>
            <fig frame="all" >
                <title>Flower placement="break"&amp;align="center"</title>
                <image href="image/flower.gif" alt="Flower" placement="break" align="center"/>
            </fig>
            <p></p>
            <fig frame="all" >
                <title>Flower placement="break"&amp;align="rifht"</title>
                <image href="image/flower.gif" alt="Flower" placement="break" align="right"/>
            </fig>
            <p></p>
            <fig frame="all" >
                <title>Flower placement="break"&amp;align="left"</title>
                <image href="image/flower.gif" alt="Flower" placement="break" align="left"/>
            </fig>
            <p></p>
            <fig frame="all" >
                <title>Flower placement="break"&amp;align="current"</title>
                <image href="image/flower.gif" alt="Flower" placement="break" align="current"/>
            </fig>
        </section>
        <section>
            <title>Jpeg sample</title>
            <fig frame="all" >
                <title>Dragon</title>
                <image href="image/dragon.jpg" alt="Dragon"/>
            </fig>
        </section>
        <section>
            <title>figgroup sample from dita1.2</title>
            <fig frame="all">
              <title>Sample complex figure</title>
              <figgroup>
                <title>First group</title>
                <ph>These elements</ph>
                <ph>are grouped together</ph>
                <ph>for some purpose</ph>
              </figgroup>
              <figgroup>
                <title>Second group</title>
                <ph>name="MetaItem" value="13"</ph>
                <ph>name="MetaThing" value="31"</ph>
                <ph>These elements</ph>
                <ph>are grouped with associated metadata</ph>
              </figgroup>
            </fig>         
            <fig frame="all">
              <title>Sample complex figure (2)</title>
              <figgroup>
                <title>First group</title>
                <ph>These elements</ph>
                <ph>are grouped together</ph>
                <ph>for some purpose</ph>
              </figgroup>
              <figgroup>
                <!--title>Second group</title-->
                <ph>name="MetaItem" value="13"</ph>
                <ph>name="MetaThing" value="31"</ph>
                <ph>These elements</ph>
                <ph>are grouped with associated metadata</ph>
              </figgroup>
            </fig>         
            <fig>
              <title>Sample complex figure (3): no frame</title>
              <figgroup>
                <title>First group</title>
                <ph>These elements</ph>
                <ph>are grouped together</ph>
                <ph>for some purpose</ph>
              </figgroup>
              <figgroup>
                <title>Second group</title>
                <ph>name="MetaItem" value="13"</ph>
                <ph>name="MetaThing" value="31"</ph>
                <ph>These elements</ph>
                <ph>are grouped with associated metadata</ph>
              </figgroup>
            </fig>         
        </section>
    </body>
